The error message you are encountering indicates that TypeScript does not recognize the `msSaveOrOpenBlob` method on the `Navigator` interface. This is because `msSaveOrOpenBlob` is a method specific to Internet Explorer and may not be available on all browsers or in all TypeScript typings.

To resolve this issue, you can add a type assertion to inform TypeScript that the `Navigator` object may have the `msSaveOrOpenBlob` method. Here is an example of how you can do this:

```typescript
// Check if msSaveOrOpenBlob exists on Navigator
if ((window.navigator as any).msSaveOrOpenBlob) {
  // Call msSaveOrOpenBlob method
  (window.navigator as any).msSaveOrOpenBlob(blob, fileName);
}
```

By using `(window.navigator as any)` you are telling TypeScript to treat `window.navigator` as a more generic type that may have additional properties or methods that are not defined in the standard `Navigator` interface.

Please note that using type assertion can suppress TypeScript's type checking, so make sure to test your code thoroughly on different browsers to ensure compatibility.

